Real-time Log Monitoring Script (log.sh)
This script monitors a log file in real-time and automatically highlights lines containing the word "error".

#!/bin/bash

# Sets the target log file path
log_file=${log_file:-/var/log/messages}

# tail -f follows the file as new lines are added
tail -f $log_file | while read line
do
    # Greps each line for the keyword "error"
    if echo $line | grep "error"; then
        echo "Error detected: $line"
    fi
done


Key Concepts:

Event-Driven Automation: Instead of manually scanning logs, the script reacts the moment an error occurs.

While Loops: The while read line loop processes the continuous stream of data coming from the tail -f command line-by-line.
